   Under state law, McClanahan's non-resident status limits her
share of ownership to 49.9 percent.
   Limited gambling in the historic Black Hills mining town was
authorized under a constitutional amendment voters approved last
year. Only blackjack, poker and slot machines are allowed, and bets
may not exceed $5.
