<FIRST>r i PM-BalloonAccident     10-07 0142</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Balloon Accident,0145</SECOND>
<HEAD>Six Injured in Australian Balloon Crash</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MELBOURNE, Australia (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A hot air balloon crash-landed in
southeastern Australia today, injuring six people, police said. It
was the second such accident in Australia in less than two months.
   Police said the balloon had been in the air about two hours when
it fell to earth about 30 miles northwest of Melbourne. Three of
the six were seriously injured, police said.
   No other details were immediately available.
   On Aug. 13, two balloons on a sightseeing trip struck each other
over central Australia, causing one to plummet 2,000 feet to the
ground and killing all 13 aboard.
   An ballooning expert called the accident in August near the town
of Alice Springs the worst in the history of the sport. The
government banned ballooning in the area until it completed its
investigation.
</TEXT>
