<HEAD>Davis Had a Comment on Many of Her Colleagues</HEAD>
<HEAD>With PM-Obit-Davis</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   Bette Davis, who died at age 81 of cancer on Friday, had the
following to say about her colleagues when she appeared at a news
conference Sept. 21 at the 37th San Sebastian Film Festival in San
Sebastian, Spain:
   Ronald Reagan: ``He never had much talent but as President he
restored patriotism for Americans.''
   James Stewart: ``I never should have let him get away.''
   Spencer Tracy: ``The greatest.''
   Joan Crawford: ``When we worked together we disappointed the
entire American press which expected us to pull each other's hair
out. Nothing like that happened and we had a very friendly
relationship.''
   Errol Flynn: ``Very handsome and a very honest and nice man
since he was aware of how badly he acted his roles.''
   Miriam Hopkins: ``We had a disastrous relationship since she was
eaten up by professional jealousy.''
