<HEAD>Heat Wave in Texas</HEAD>
<HEAD>By The Associated Press</HEAD>
<TEXT>
   Rain dampened parts of Virginia and Pennsylvania today and
temperatures dropped across the Midwest.
   Temperatures soared into the 80s and 90s Friday from
south-central Texas to the southern Atlantic Coast states, setting
records for the date in Austin and Corpus Christi, Texas, where the
temperature reached 96 degrees.
   Strong northerly winds ushered cold Canadian air into the Great
Plains and the Great Lakes region early today, where highs were in
the 40s and 50s.
   Showers and thunderstorms developing along the leading edge of
the cold front were scattered from central Texas across Arkansas
into Pennsylvania.
   Cloudy skies prevailed from the northern and central Rockies
into the northern Plains, and across much of the Great Lakes region
and the Northeast Friday.
   Other reports:
   _East: Albany, N.Y. 55 cloudy; Atlanta 69 fair; Boston 62
cloudy; Charleston, S.C. 74 fair; Chattanooga 68 cloudy; Cincinnati
