<FIRST>r i AM-BRF--Britain-ConsentAge     10-07 0130</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-BRF--Britain-Consent Age,0133</SECOND>
<HEAD>Labor Party Votes to Lower Age of Consent for Homosexuals</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BRIGHTON, England (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The opposition Labor party voted at its
annual conference to lower the age of consent for homosexuals from
21 to 16, the legal age for heterosexuals.
   The vote Friday was 3.7 million to 2.3 million.
   The age of consent is the minimum age at which a person may
legally have sexual intercourse.
   During a Thursday debate on the matter, party member Debbie
Epstein, a supporter of the Labor Campaign for Lesbian and Gay
Rights, said: ``Equality shouldn't be a difficult concept for
socialists to grasp.''
   Labor's policy-making National Executive Committee will decide
whether the proposal will be included in the party's election
manifesto.
   The governing Conservatives must call general elections before
mid-1992.
