<HEAD>Three Children Die After Climbing in Freezer</HEAD>
<DATELINE>METZ, Mo. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Three young cousins suffocated after they
climbed into an abandoned freezer while playing near a relative's
house, authorities said.
   The children's bodies were found in the chest freezer in a barn
Friday night by a sheriff's deputy. The childen were reported
missing from the relative's house five miles west of Metz in
western Missouri.
   Vernon County Sheriff Brian Atkinson said the lid of the freezer
automatically locked when it shut. He said it was unclear whether
the children pulled it shut or whether it fell shut accidentally.
   The children were identified as Tanya Cathey, 5; her 4-year-old
brother, David Cathey; and their cousin, 5-year-old Natalie Ellis.
