<HEAD>Senate Confirms Controversial Nominations</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The Senate on Saturday confirmed Melvin
Sembler to be ambassador to Australia and Della Newman to be
ambassador to New Zealand, accepting two of President Bush's
nominees despite criticism over their political connections.
   The Senate confirmed them on a voice vote, with Sen. Paul
Sarbanes, D-Md., a critic of the quality of Bush's ambassadorial
appointments, saying he continued to oppose the Sembler and Newman
nominations.
