numerous ambassadorships to people who were unqualified for the
posts but well-connected politically.
   Sembler, a Florida shopping center tycoon, donated $127,000 to
Bush's 1988 presidential campaign, Sarbanes said earlier this year
in opposing his nomination.
   Newman, a real estate broker from Seattle, Wash., was chairman
of Bush's Washington state campaign and is a longtime friend of the
Bush family.
