<HEAD>Noriega's Michigan Pen Pal Prepares for Panamanian Vacation</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEGAUNEE, Mich. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An 11-year-old girl prepared Saturday for
a trip that she hoped would include a visit with her pen pal, Gen.
Manuel Antonio Noriega of Panama.
   Sarah York and her mother first visited Noriega last year at the
general's invitation after the general and the youngster struck up
a friendship through the mail.
   ``The only things that are left are the suitcases and I'm
getting those ready now,'' Pauline York said Saturday, on the eve
of her daughter's and husband's trip to the troubled Central
American nation. They're due back to Negaunee, on Michigan's Upper
