Noriega, who put down a coup attempt Tuesday.
   ``Our friends there have reassured us that everything in Panama
is OK now,'' she said. ``They would have told her if it was a bad
time for them to come.''
   Sarah first wrote Noriega in March 1988, after seeing him on
television, saying she wanted to learn more about his country.
After a correspondence, Noriega paid for Sarah to visit on a
five-day trip. This second trip, however, was paid for by the York
family.
